                    </div>
                    <span>I gave this movie 5 stars. It is the first movie that actually made me cry! 
<br />First, it takes place in a nursing home. Noah is reading the notebook to his wife, Allie. Allie has a deisease where she forgets things, and even forgets people.
<br />In the beginning, it takes place in the 1940's in North Carolina. There is a rich girl named Allie, and a boy poor named Noah. In the beginning, Noah really likes Allie, but Allie dosen't really like him. Noah asks her on a date by hanging on a bar at the ferris wheel at the carnival. Allie says no, but Noah is about to slip, so she says yes. They go on a date and dance in the streets. Allie's parents do not like Noah, and want her to date someone who is rich. They are still in love. When it is time for Allie to move out of her summer home, Noah writes a letter to her everyday of the year, for one year. Her mother hides the letter from Allie, because she dosen't like Noah. Allie dosen't know that he even sent her letters. As time goes on, Noah buys a old house that Allie said she would love to have. Though he has not seen her in a while, he makes the house the way Allie would like it, even the blue shutters she wanted. In the meantime, Allie is getting married to a very rich man named Lon. On (Or near) her wedding day, she sees an atricle about Noah in the newspaper, and a photo of his home. She wanted to see Noah, so she goes back to North Carolina to see him. They end up falling in love again.
<br /> All I will tell you is that the ending is a bit of a suprise, and VEERRRRRRRYYYYY sad!
<br /> I would suggest this movie for anyone about 12 and up. I am 11, though. There is some breif nudity, some cursing and lots of making out.</span>
                  
